summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of Prospect Avenue from the northerly line of Price Street to the southerly line of Elve Street et al, West Seattle, now in the City of Seattle, by constructing concrete sidewalks under Ordinance No. 16, creating Local Improvement District No. W-6 prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement.
